{"lemma":"ناسُ","slug":"ناسُ","root":"ن.#.س","root_slug":"ن-_-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-_-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ناس","root":"أنس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":241},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40740","n40743"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"people, humans","tags":["plural","plural-only"],"examples":[{"text":"كَثِيرٌ مِنْ النَّاسِ فِي السُّوقِ.","english":"There are many people in the market."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dangle, to swing, to quiver","tags":["plural","plural-only"],"examples":[{"text":"مَا ٱلَّذِي سَيَقُولُهُ ٱلْآنَ لِهٰذَا ٱلصَّحَفِيِّ ٱلشَّابِّ ٱلَّذِي يَنُوسُ بِرَأْسِهِ مِنْ ثِقَلِ ٱلسُّكْرِ","english":"Now, what would he tell this young journalist, whose head was lolling drunkenly."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Back-formation from النَّاس (an-nās), contraction of الْأُنَاس (al-ʔunās). Cognate with Aramaic אֲנָשָׁא (ʾănāšā), Classical Syriac ܐܲܢܵܫܵܐ, ܢܵܫܵܐ (ʾanāšā, nāšā), Biblical Hebrew אֱנוֹשׁ (ʾĕnōš) (whence English Enos)."},"ipa":["/naːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40740","headword_ar":"نَاسَ","root":"nws","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanuwsu","text_ar":"يَنُوسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawosN","text_ar":"نَوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawasaAnN","text_ar":"نَوَسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, M, as a look of hair, and an carring, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moved to and fro;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was in a state of commotion, and moved to and fro,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hanging down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it dangled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hung down and was in a state of commotion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agitation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb [but in the M, the verb in this last sense has only the former of the two inf. ns. assigned to it, though the other equally helongs to it.]) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsa luEaAbuhu","text_ar":"نَاسَ لُعَابُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His slaver flowed and was in a state of commotion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See also 5]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n40743","headword_ar":"نَاسٌ","root":"nws","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii;"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2867},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) but its predominant application is to the former: (Msb:) it is said by some to be applied to both in the former of the last two verses of the Kur,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@l~a*iY yuwasowisu fiY Suduwri Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"ا@لَّذِى يُوَسْوِسُ فِى صُدُورِ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Aljin~api waAln~aAsi","text_ar":"مِنَ الجِنَّةِ وَالنَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who suggesteth what is vain in the breasts of people of the jinn and mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; unless by it be meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsiY","text_ar":"النَّاسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the forgetting]; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn Aljn~p wAlnAs","text_ar":"من الجنّة والناس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added in explanation of a preceding word,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwasowaAs","text_ar":"الوَسْوَاس"},{"kind":"text","text":", or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*Y","text_ar":"الذى"},{"kind":"text","text":", or it is in dependence upon"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ywsws","text_ar":"يوسوس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Bd;) [but what corroborates the first explanation is the fact that] men and jinn are both termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAl","text_ar":"رِجَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur, lxxii. 6; and the Arabs used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu naAsFA","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ نَاسًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Aljin~i","text_ar":"مِنَ الجِنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw people of the jinn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) it is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unaAsN","text_ar":"اُنَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) a pl. which is rare [as to form]; (K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unaAsN","text_ar":"اُنَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ns","text_ar":"انس"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAs","text_ar":"ناس"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to it, (S, M,) but not as a substitute for the suppressed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", because, were it so, it would not be found prefixed to the original,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unaAsN","text_ar":"اُنَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whereas it is found prefixed to this latter: (S:) this derivation, however, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unaAsN","text_ar":"اُنَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", contradicts its belonging to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nws","text_ar":"نوس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF;) [but some hold that it does belong to this art.; and the form of its dim., to be mentioned below, favours their opinion: Fei says,] it is a noun applied to denote a pl., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahoTN","text_ar":"رَهْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from a different root: it is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsa","text_ar":"نَاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanuwsu","text_ar":"يَنُوسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “ it hung down and was in a state of commotion: ” and [agreeably with this derivation it is said that] its dim. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwayosN","text_ar":"نُوَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) some, again, said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsiY","text_ar":"النَّاسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout.       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwaAsN","text_ar":"نُوَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","M"]}]}}